==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Sturdy adhesive tape, usually black and 48mm (2 inches)wide, made of plastic reinforced with cross-linked fibre.  Derives from the tape used to attach lighting and microphones to the long poles needed to place these in optimal position during film-making (''see Gaffer'')

Synonyms: Duct tape; Duck tape. The latter is probably a mispronunciation. Duct tape must be waterproof: gaffer tape must withstand high temperatures

